$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex je okrajšava za Hexadecimal, ki temelji na strukturi osnove -16 in se uporablja za poenostavitev načina predstavitve navodil računalnikom. Ta 16-simbolni številski sistem je bil razvit kot sredstvo za preprečevanje 8-bitnega binarnega števila, tako da je mogoče podatke brez težav kodirati v računalnike. Lahko ga vtisnete in vtipkate z dvema različnima šestnajstiškima števkama, pri čemer vsaka šestnajstiška številka predstavlja nibble ali morda 4-bitni format.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Ta številski sistem uporablja 16 simbolov, ki so predstavljeni v razponu od 0-9 ali AF. 0–9 predstavljajo številke do devet, medtem ko je AF predstavljen s številkami 10–15. V primerjavi z ostalimi tremi vrstami številskih sistemov se šestnajstiški sistem šteje za najučinkovitejšega.';
